[thinking] **Clarifying dependency scopes**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm analyzing runtime dependencies that appear on testRuntimeClasspath but not on testCompileClasspath. It seems that the native-image compile and run likely includes the runtime. For deterministic dependencies, it makes sense that the driver can only add testImplementation, not runtimeOnly. If tests require wagon-specific classes, testImplementation becomes necessary. But typically, generated tests shouldn’t import runtime provider classes unless they need to cover component loading. I'm realizing that the setup entries only list testImplementation dependencies. It's all a bit complex!
