nsidering whether we should only be testing full Maven build execution if there’s meaningful coverage. If the generated tests invoke MavenCli with no local repository, our approach might need to change. I wonder if we could use advisory_preparation for better guidance on the environment, system properties, or test setup. The setup seems to involve extra Maven dependencies, Docker images, or environment properties that generated tests should set. I need to represent these appropriately in our deterministic setup entries.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GBDdFIwv0OIgcRCC4y7Kq9CO|fc_0dd18210c76a8fb9016a40a8833b848190b06f2a1cf124ff94", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport zipfile, os\nj=os.path.expanduser('~/.m2/repository/org/apache/maven/maven-core/2.0.7/maven-core-2.0.7-sources.jar')\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(j) as z:\n    for name in ['META-INF/plexus/plexus.xml','META-INF/plexus/components.xml']:\n        txt=z.read(name).decode('utf-8', errors='ignore')\n        print(name, 'contains maven.home?', 'maven.home' in txt, 'env?', 'env.' in txt)\nPY", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 912, "output": 815, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27839, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782622329329, "responseId": "resp_0dd18210c76a8fb9016a40a879d2fc8190a54ad349e766cb0e"}}
